A 37-YEAR-OLD man allegedly stabbed a 57-year-old to death after catching him with his girlfriend. The man allegedly followed his girlfriend and found her with the older man in Vaal Park, Free State, on Monday, 25 July. The police said he stabbed him with a sharp object and then ran on foot, leaving the girlfriend at the scene. Cops and emergency services were called but declared the victim dead at he scene. ALSO READ | MAMFUNDISI: Ujola with my pastor hubby! The suspect was arrested on the same day, and was due to appear in court on Wednesday, 27 July, for murder and Contravention of the Immigration Act Constable Langa Maselela said: “Preliminary investigations suggest that he is not South African, but everything will be finalised when he appears in court.” The police have urged anyone who may have witnessed the incident to call CrimeStop on 08600 10111.